FBIS4-41734 "drsov124_v_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 Lithuania Opinion Poll Shows Loss of Support for Leaders Opinion Poll Shows Loss of Support for Leaders WS2806092194 Tallinn BNS in English 1822 GMT 27 Jun 94 WS2806092194 Tallinn BNS English BFN [Text] Vilnius, Jun 27, BNS -- Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas' popularity rating increased by 2 percent in June after a sharp drop in May, according to the results of a public opinion poll conducted June 8-15 by the British-Lithuanian Baltic Surveys. But the survey indicates that Lithuanians continue to lose confidence in nearly all other political leaders, with the exception of the chairman of the opposition Conservative Party's board, Gediminas Vagnorius, whose rating jumped by 5 percent. Vagnorius is now ahead of Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius and the Conservative Party leader, Vytautas Landsbergis. Centrists Egidijus Bickauskas and Romualdas Ozolas retained second and third positions. Like earlier, the popularity lists ends with Foreign Minister Povilas Gylys, even though his popularity went up by 1 percent. According to the results, the most popular politicians in June were: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Algirdas Brazauskas |55 percent |(+2) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Egidijus Bickauskas |49 |(0) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Romualdas Ozolas |43 |(+1) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Gediminas Vagnorius |34 |(+5) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Vytautas Landsbergis |34 |(0) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Adolfas Slezevicius |28 |(-3) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Ceslovas Jursenas |37 |(-3) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Aloyzas Sakalas |26 |(0) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Algirdas Saudargas |23 |(-3) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Povilas Gylys |19 |(+1) | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
